{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17623268","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17623268"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:09:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:09:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16853"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16853","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16853"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.76,0.15,0.07,0,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9543"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75270"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9543","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9543"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16853"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60778"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1003"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"9833"},{"type":"tags","id":"9834"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22548"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22553"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75270"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe coagulation cascade can be considered as separate pathways that converge to form a common pathway. The cascade leads to fibrin production and subsequent blood clot formation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the initial step of the intrinsic coagulation pathway?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Factor XII activation by contact with negatively charged surfaces","Factor VII binding to tissue factor","Thrombin cleaving fibrinogen","Factor VIII activation by thrombin","Factor X activation by factor IXa"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe intrinsic coagulation pathway begins with \u003Cstrong\u003Efactor XII (Hageman factor) activation by contact with negatively charged surfaces\u003C/strong\u003E such as \u003Cstrong\u003Ecollagen \u003C/strong\u003Eor \u003Cstrong\u003Eartificial materials\u003C/strong\u003E. This is why the intrinsic pathway is also known as the contact activation pathway. This activated factor XII then triggers a cascade of subsequent factor activations leading to fibrin production.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFactor VII binding to tissue factor\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the initiating step of the extrinsic pathway, not the intrinsic pathway\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFactor X activation by factor IXa\u003C/strong\u003E - This occurs later in the intrinsic pathway cascade, not at the beginning\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThrombin cleaving fibrinogen\u003C/strong\u003E - This is part of the common pathway, occurring after both intrinsic and extrinsic pathways converge\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFactor VIII activation by thrombin\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a feedback mechanism that occurs later in the cascade, not the initiating step\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter factor XII activation, the intrinsic pathway proceeds through sequential activation of factors XI, IX, and VIII, ultimately leading to factor X activation and joining the common pathway.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The intrinsic coagulation pathway begins when factor XII is activated by contact with negatively charged surfaces.","The intrinsic pathway involves sequential activation of factors XII, XI, IX, and VIII leading to factor X activation.","The intrinsic pathway and the extrinsic pathway converge to become the common pathway"],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Smith SA, Travers RJ, Morrissey JH. How it all starts: Initiation of the clotting cascade. Crit Rev Biochem Mol Biol. 2015;50(4):326-336. doi:10.3109/10409238.2015.1050550"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60778"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16853"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60778","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60778"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T15:44:34+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T15:45:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9543"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75270"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"